The paper deals with learning games from observations of strategic interactions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The method proposed in the paper involves regularized logistic regression, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the sample complexity of learning the games, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the separability conditions on the payoff matrices, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper includes simulation experiments to verify the theoretical results, which is a topic in computational social science (cs.SI).
